        "Id": "mechdef_cyclopsii_CPII-X3",
        "Name": "Cyclops II",
        "Details": "After the chaos of the Jihad and the Wars of Reaving, Grumium Creations saw an opportunity to revitalize the venerable Cyclops design with a ground up redesign that would make use of Clan-spec tech throughout, while still retaining the command equipment the Cyclops was known for. This redesign, dubbed the Cyclops II, was increased to 95 tons, used a Clan-spec endosteel chassis and a Clan-spec 380-XL engine and XL gyro to maintain the same speed profile of the original Cyclops, and the head was still fitted with the originals highly effective Tacticon computer. Each general variant of this 'Mech was equipped with some type of C3 system, with the B sub-variant (this one) having a C3i Computer for use with small lance level combat forces. The 3 general variant is built for massive missile volleys, a trio of IATM 9s with 5 tons of ammo provide the primary closer in firepower, while the LRM 20 and up to 4 LRM 5 (depending on which C3 system is fitted) provide secondary fire support with another 5 tons of ammo.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
        "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_ioncyclops"
    },
